\par }\pard \ltrpar\qj \fi-2\li0\ri-2\sl1\slmult0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\hyphpar0\aspalpha\aspnum\fahang\frmtxbtlr\outlinelevel0\adjustright\rin-2\lin0\itap0\cufi-1\culi-1\pararsid9377821 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f0\insrsid1191976 ABSTRACT: }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\insrsid9377821\charrsid9377821 This study analyzes the representation of patriarchal culture in Oka Rusmini\rquote s novel Tarian Bumi using a qualitative approach throug
h content analysis. The main focus of the research lies in examining how patriarchal values are institutionalized in Balinese society, particularly through customary systems, caste structures, and family hierarchies. These elements shape women\rquote 
s social pos
itions and greatly influence their bodily autonomy and personal freedom. The findings indicate that the novel not only portrays the various forms of oppression experienced by women under patriarchal domination but also highlights the resistance expressed 
b
y its female characters. Such resistance is reflected in their efforts to challenge social constructions, assert their identities, and negotiate space within restrictive cultural environments. Moreover, Tarian Bumi functions as a literary medium capable o
f
 deconstructing the myths that sustain patriarchal culture. Through its depiction of complex female experiences, the novel encourages readers to critically reflect on gender inequality embedded in cultural and social practices. Thus, the work contributes 
to a broader understanding of the importance of emancipation and gender justice, emphasizing literature\rquote s role in questioning deeply rooted norms and fostering transformative social awareness.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\insrsid5270098 

